ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Core courses, though a little hard.

I feel like this class has a lot of very important information to offer. It is A LOT of work and a very large time commitment. At the end of the day Professor Rosner really cares that his students learn the material, and goes out of his way to make sure that we learn it.
I will recommend it to other students, because it combined theory and application in separation process.
Yes. It is extremely helpful for chemical engineering.

Fast-paced overview of current and emerging separation processes. I would absolutely recommend to any student since it is a very approachable overview of the field without requiring any specialization or even a Chem Eng degree.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I didn't realize how much I learned until I turned in my final. I learned more about both separation processes and engineering that I every thought possible in one class.
This course inspired me to write a new grant.
